articles.author: Gabriella Borter
articles.description: An hour after Rabbi Jonathan Leener put out a call for donations among his small Brooklyn synagogue community, he had raised $5,000. Soon he had taken in enough supplies to fill an SUV.
articles.title: With bulletproof vests, socks and soap, US Jews rush to aid Israel

articles.author: Emily Rose, Ilan Rosenberg
articles.description: Israeli paramedic Hami Atias has seen much death and gore over 21 years of treating victims of violent attacks, natural disasters and war wounded. But the scene that greeted him at a leafy kibbutz near Gaza at the weekend will haunt him forever.
articles.title: Gore, gunfights and hostage-taking scar kibbutz dwellers

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Yifat Zailer wishes she could travel back in time to Friday.
articles.title: In Israel, one woman still searching for news of six missing family members

articles.author: Idrees Ali
articles.description: The U.S. military has yet to see any sign that other Israeli adversaries are preparing to move against Israel following a surprise attack by the Palestinian militant group Hamas, General C.Q. Brown, chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, said on Wednesday.
articles.title: Top US general: No indications other Israeli adversaries to join war

articles.author: Ahmed Mohamed Hassan
articles.description: Egypt has discussed plans with the United States and others to provide humanitarian aid through its border with Gaza Strip but rejects any move to set up safe corridors for refugees fleeing the enclave, Egyptian security sources said on Wednesday.
articles.title: Egypt discusses Gaza aid, rejects corridors for civilians, say sources

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Butcher Tali Yehuda says her tears are with the families of those who have perished as she firmly sticks in a pin to secure a yellow sunflower into one of hundreds of wreaths being prepared by volunteers for funerals across Israel.
articles.title: Israeli volunteers prepare hundreds of wreaths for funerals

articles.author: Humeyra Pamuk
articles.description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken headed to Israel on Wednesday on a Middle East mission to prevent a wider war from erupting after an attack and hostage-taking by Palestinian Hamas militants and an Israeli bombardment of the Gaza Strip.
articles.title: Blinken to Israel on Middle East mission to prevent a wider war

articles.author: Jeff Mason, Maayan Lubell, Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden on Wednesday warned Iran against getting involved in Israel's conflict with Hamas amid fears of a wider regional conflict, while Israeli leaders formed an emergency war cabinet to present a united front.
articles.title: Biden warns Iran over Gaza; Israel forms emergency war cabinet

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Most of the 2.3 million people in the Gaza Strip have no electricity and no water. And, with hundreds of Israeli strikes raining down on their tiny enclave, they have nowhere to run.
articles.title: Gazans bombarded by Israel have no hope and no escape

articles.author: Raphael Satter
articles.description: Internet companies Google, Amazon and Cloudflare say they have weathered the internet's largest-known denial of service attack and are sounding the alarm over a new technique they warn could easily cause widespread disruption.
articles.title: Internet companies report biggest-ever denial of service operation
